{"key":"post-13785619","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13785619</id>\n<content>Spent coffee grinds should be laid out and dried for storage.&amp;nbsp; Don't store them wet or they'll mold.&amp;nbsp; When using dry coffee grinds in a substrate, mix them all together and pasteurize.&amp;nbsp; Don't sterilize coffee and then use it in a bulk substrate.&amp;nbsp; Not only is this a duplication of work, it is counterproductive and will lead to a higher contamination rate.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13786469</next>\n<prev>13785228</prev>\n<first>13773937</first>\n<last>14503417</last>\n<when>1295028891</when>\n<utime>01/14/11 08:14 PM</utime>\n</post>"}